#dat <-dat[-1]
dat$DOW <- as.factor(dat$DOW)
dat$DH_Game <- as.factor(dat$DH_Game)
# dat$Year <- as.factor(dat$Year)
dat$Away <- as.factor(dat$Away)
dat$Game_Time <- as.factor(dat$Game_Time)
dat <- dummy_cols(dat, select_columns = c("DOW","DH_Game", "Away", "Game_Time"))
dat$DOW <- NULL
dat$DH_Game <- NULL
# dat$Year <- NULL
dat$Away <- NULL
dat$Game_Time <- NULL



dat$home_win_perc <- dat$H_Wins/dat$H_Game_number
dat$away_win_perc <- dat$A_Wins/dat$A_Game_number
dat$top_starter <- ifelse(dat$H_Start == "Justin Verlander",1,ifelse(dat$H_Start ==  "Max Scherzer",1,0))
dat <- dat[-1]


# normalize <- function(x) {
#   return ((x - min(x)) / (max(x) - min(x)))
# }
# dat[,c(1:2,4:55)] <- as.data.frame(lapply(dat[,c(1:2,4:55)], normalize))
## 75% of the sample size
smp_size <- floor(0.75 * nrow(dat))

## set the seed to make your partition reproducible
# set.seed(124)
train_ind <- sample(seq_len(nrow(dat)), size = smp_size)
train <-dat[train_ind, ]
test <- dat[-train_ind, ]
#with bagging
library(randomForest)
## randomForest 4.6-14
## Type rfNews() to see new features/changes/bug fixes.

## Attaching package: 'randomForest'

#Random Forest
rf <- randomForest(Attendance ~.,data = train, importance = TRUE, ntree = 1000)
rf
## 
## Call:
##  randomForest(formula = Attendance ~ ., data = train, importance = TRUE,      ntree = 1000) 
##                Type of random forest: regression
##                      Number of trees: 1000
## No. of variables tried at each split: 18
## 
##           Mean of squared residuals: 23535418
##                     % Var explained: 63.4
varImpPlot(rf, n.var =10)

model.rf.predictions <- predict(rf, test)
model.rf.predictions <- as.integer(round(model.rf.predictions))
oosmae_rf <- abs((test$Attendance-model.rf.predictions))
summary(oosmae_rf)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##      18    1473    3052    3827    5308   25554
oosmse_rf <- mean((test$Attendance-model.rf.predictions)^2)
summary(oosmse_rf)
##     Min.  1st Qu.   Median     Mean  3rd Qu.     Max. 
## 25738773 25738773 25738773 25738773 25738773 25738773
rf_pred_error <- test$Attendance-model.rf.predictions

plot(x=test$Attendance, y=model.rf.predictions,

# Linear

anslin = predict(linmodel, newdata=test)

#PDP

steps = 30
f_hat <- matrix(0,steps+1,4)
for(x in c(1:7,54:56)){
  f_hat <- matrix(0,steps+1,4)
  plot_data <- train[-5]
  x_max <- max(plot_data[,x])
  x_min <- min(plot_data[,x])
  j= x_min
  r=1
  while(j <= x_max){
    plot_data[,x] = j
    tmp_rf = predict(rf,newdata = plot_data,type="response")
    tmp_glm = predict(glm_p,newdata = plot_data,type="response")
    tmp_svm =  predict(model.1, plot_data)
    f_hat[r,1] = j
    f_hat[r,2] = mean(tmp_rf)
    f_hat[r,3] = mean(tmp_glm)
    f_hat[r,4] = mean(tmp_svm)

    j = j + (x_max-x_min)/steps
    r=r+1
  }
  if(x == 54 || x == 55){
    plot(f_hat[2:steps,1],f_hat[2:steps,2], type = "l" , col = "green", main = colnames(plot_data[x]), xlab = "Factor Value", ylab = "Pred Resp." )
  lines(f_hat[2:steps,1],f_hat[2:steps,3], type = "l" ,col = "black", main = colnames(plot_data[x]), xlab = "Factor Value", ylab = "Pred Resp." )
  lines(f_hat[2:steps,1],f_hat[2:steps,4], type = "l" ,col = "red", main = colnames(plot_data[x]), xlab = "Factor Value", ylab = "Pred Resp." )
  }else{
  plot(f_hat[2:steps,1],f_hat[2:steps,3], type = "l" , main = colnames(plot_data[x]), xlab = "Factor Value", ylab = "Pred Resp." )
  lines(f_hat[2:steps,1],f_hat[2:steps,2], type = "l" ,col = "green", main = colnames(plot_data[x]), xlab = "Factor Value", ylab = "Pred Resp." )
  lines(f_hat[2:steps,1],f_hat[2:steps,4], type = "l" ,col = "red", main = colnames(plot_data[x]), xlab = "Factor Value", ylab = "Pred Resp." )
  }
}
